    "The corresponding kernel function for any two observations in such a merged light curve is,",
    "where k latent denotes the kernel of the underlying latent GP.",
    "S 1 and S 2 are the variability-amplitude scaling factors for the corresponding photometric bands, and τ lag represents the relative time lag between them.",
    "The variability amplitude in each band is obtained by multiplying the latent GP amplitude by the corresponding scaling factor.",
    "This class of kernel functions, as expressed in Equation 5, has seen broad application in astronomical time series analysis (e.g., Gordon et al. 2020; Villar et al. 2021)."
